    "The reported data scaling methods require knowledge of the statistical properties of the entire dataset, which might not be available in real-time.",
    "Windowing is also quite important because using sliding windows would require a trade-off between having sufficient samples for the ML algorithm to function properly and not introducing large time delays, which could affect the overall user experience; while using ever expanding windows would be inefficient.",
